Opportunity to discuss directly with APUI Education Group, Poland
In November at Duc Anh Company, APUI's admissions director will discuss with parents, students the degree program, scholarship ... when studying in Poland.
04 Nov 2019, 09:10 by VnExpress
The strengths of studying abroad in Poland are reasonable tuition and living expenses, 10-100% scholarships, quality European education, good living and security environment, friendly cooperation between the two Governments, The Vietnamese community in Poland is large and supports good students, transferring from Vietnamese universities to Poland or Poland to other developed countries, training in English ...
In November, Mr. Hazar - Admissions Director of APUI Group - Association of Polish Universities for Internationalization will come to Vietnam to meet and discuss directly with parents and students about the curriculum, entry requirements, scholarships, tuition, help them plan and prepare the best for study abroad in Poland.

Event time and venue:

- Ho Chi Minh City: 16h-18h, November 12 at Duc Anh building, 172 Bui Thi Xuan, District 1;
- Hanoi: 16h-18h, November 13 at Duc Anh building, 54-56 Tue Tinh.
Register here to receive information about studying abroad before attending the event. For more information, contact the hotline: 09887 09698 and email: duhoc@ducanh.edu.vn
In addition, if you are interested and want to learn about studying abroad in Europe, you can attend the Study Abroad Europe Conference: UK, Switzerland, Netherlands, Italy, Germany, Poland.

The event is held at:

Hanoi: 15h-18h, November 9 at LOpera hotel, 29 Trang Tien, Hoan Kiem district;
Ho Chi Minh City: 9am-12pm, November 10 at Lotte Legend Hotel Saigon, 2A-4A Ton Duc Thang Street, Ben Nghe, District 1.
Detailed information about the event, see here.




APUI Corporation, Poland

- An association of 5 universities in Poland. Through collaborative activities and projects, APUI aims to attract more and more international students:
- Supporting universities in the process of developing international student and faculty exchanges, promoting universities abroad and participating in the building of a global knowledge society;
- Encouraging many universities to open English programs to attract international students
- There are programs taught in English at all levels;
- Reasonable tuition, from 1,700 - 4,000 Euro / year;
- Living expenses: 4,000-7,000 Euro / year;
- Polish Government allows international students to work overtime 40 hours / week;
- Stay a year to look for a job after graduation and a permanent job, settle when eligible.
See full information about studying in Poland here

Training programs at APUI


Academic level:

- English / University Preparation - for those who do not have enough English;
- Bachelor;
- Master degree.

5 APUI universities and training majors:

- University of Business in Wroclaw (University of Business in Wroclaw): is a private university, located in Warsaw. Training School:
Bachelor: Management, Computer Engineering, Tourism and Entertainment;
Master: Management, Tourism and Entertainment.
- Olsztyńska Szkoła Wyższa im. Józefa Rusieckiego: is a private university, founded in 1997, located in Olsztyn. Training School:
Bachelor: Physiotherapy, Cosmetology, Education, English Studies, Physical Education;
Master: Physical Therapy, Education, Physical Education.
- Vistula University: is a private university, founded in 1996, located in Warsaw. Training School:
Bachelor: Diet, Economics, Finance and Accounting, International Relations, Management, Tourism and Entertainment, Architecture, Computer Engineering;
Master: Computer Engineering, Energy Management (Minor in Management), Accounting and Finance, International Relations, Management, Tourism and Entertainment
- University of Economics and Human Sciences (University of Economics and Human Sciences): is a private organization, founded in 2001, located in Warsaw. Training School:
Bachelor: Management, Psychology, Finance and Accounting, International Relations, Computer Engineering;
Master: Management, Finance and Accounting.
Pułtusk Academy of Humanities (Pułtusk Academy of Humanities): is a private university, founded in 1994, located in Pułtusk. Training school: Management; National security; History; Pedagogy; Political Science
For a list of specific school programs (with tuition), please see here.




Application file:

Scan from the following documents and send them to Duc Anh for evaluation and assistance:
- Academic records / transcripts of the last 2 academic years;
- High school diploma / University or temporary certification;
- English certificate - if available;
-Report - page with photos and signatures;
- Work CV - if applying for postgraduate program;
- Academic achievements, other foreign activities - if you want to apply for a scholarship.

Duc Anh A&T supports international students

Duc Anh - the study abroad consulting company of the top performing agent - supports students:
- Consultancy of school choice / industry choice;
- Check if you are eligible to enter your desired field of study;
- Please study;
- Apply for a scholarship if you qualify - very effective;
- Applying for a student visa - the rate of Duc Anh's visa is the best in Vietnam;
- Organize English test PTE A for you, see more about PTE A;
- Practice IELTS and PTE A / TOEFL for you;
- Arrangement of housing / pick up / health insurance;
- Support you during the process of studying abroad.
In particular, the first students of the Duc Anh Company to study in Poland since 2005 and are now successful.
For details on application procedures, student visas and related issues, contact: Duc Anh - Hanoi Study Abroad Consulting Company: 54-56 Tue Tinh, Tel: 024 3971 6229- HCMC: 172 Bui Thi Xuan, Tel: 028 3929 3995- General Hotline: 09887 09698- Email: duhoc@ducanh.edu.vn- Website: ducanhduhoc.vn/German Anh EduConnect: - Professional, transparent, effective study abroad markets of England, Australia, USA, New Zealand, Canada, Netherlands, Switzerland, Singapore, Malaysia, Japan; - Organize English test for PTE Academic, PTE Academic test scores equivalent and replace IELTS- TOEFL in study abroad, employment and settlement; - Academic English, high-level specialized English in Vietnam.
(Source: Duc Anh Study Abroad Consulting Company)
